Lock Screen Magazine Privacy Notice
Last updated: August 16, 2024
Update history:
We changed the operating entity of Lock Screen Magazine from BRAVO UNICORN PTE. LTD. to HEYTAP PTE. LTD.
Thank you for using Lock Screen Magazine. Lock Screen Magazine is a feature that provides users with high-quality, beautiful, and personalized images from our community for a distinctive, interactive experience. During your use of our websites, mobile apps, or other products or services, we may collect and use your personal information.
Personal information refers to all information that is recorded electronically or otherwise and can be used alone or in combination with other information to identify a specific natural person.
This Privacy Notice explains why and how Lock Screen Magazine collects your personal information, what personal information it collects from you, your rights to your personal information, and how we protect the security of your personal information.
Before using Lock Screen Magazine, please carefully read this Privacy Notice to understand our practices regarding protection of your personal information. If you do not agree to the terms of this Privacy Notice, you can exit Lock Screen Magazine by tapping "Exit" and we will not be able to provide you with the services related to Lock Screen Magazine. By tapping "Agree" to launch Lock Screen Magazine, you acknowledge that you fully understand the collection and use of personal information and your rights described below.
This Privacy Notice will help you understand:
1
How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
2
How We Retain Your Personal Information
3
How We Share, Transfer or Publicly Disclose Your Personal Information
4
How We Protect Your Personal Information
5
Your Rights to Your Personal Information
6
How We Process Children's Personal Information
7
Third-Party Service Providers and Their Services
8
How Your Personal Information Is Transferred Globally
9
How This Privacy Notice Is Updated
1.
How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
We collect personal information in order to operate more efficiently and provide you with an optimal user experience.
The personal information we collect includes: (1) information directly provided by you to us; (2) relevant information obtained during your use of Lock Screen Magazine; and/or (3) personal information about you obtained from third parties.
The information we collect depends on the products you actually use, the environment in which you interact with us, an
d the choices you make, including your privacy settings and the products and features you use. Our products and functions include core service functions and value-added service functions.
When we collect information, you do not necessarily have to provide your personal information. For core service functions, if you choose not to provide the information, we may be unable to provide you with Lock Screen Magazine services or respond to or deal with the problems you may encounter. For value-added service functions, you can choose whether or not to agree to our collection of your personal information. If you do not agree, you may not be able to use relevant value-added service functions. This, however, does not affect your use of our core service functions.
1.1
How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
(A)
We may use information about your device such as the device name, device model, device ID, region, MAC address, serial number, IP address, and operating system version to provide you with content pushes or notifications, including app updates and installations, and sales and promotional messages, etc. You may unsubscribe from our sales and promotional messages by sending us an SMS message or email or by tapping "Settings - Messages & recommendations - Notifications" on your device.
(B)
If you wish to participate in lucky draws or competitions, participate in promotional or marketing activities organized by us or our business partners, complete relevant surveys, or participate in user forums or blogs held by us or our business partners, you may need to provide us with your name,
mobile number, email address
, postal address,
bank account number
in order for us to contact you, send you rewards, and conduct user or follow-up surveys.
(C)
When providing after-sales services and customer support to you, we may request and collect your personal information, such as your device information (e.g., device ID), your name,
mobile number, email address,
postal address, and device logs, and may
record
the calls between you and our customer service representatives. We use the data to diagnose product issues, repair customers' devices, and provide other customer care and support services. We may use your email address to respond to the questions raised or comments made by you in the "Contact Us" or "Data Subject Rights Platform" section of our website.
(D)
In order to fulfill cybersecurity protection obligations, ensure the normal functioning of Lock Screen Magazine and the security of your account, and improve your user experience, we will collect the following information during your use of Lock Screen Magazine: information about your device such as the device name, device model, device ID, MAC address, serial number, IP address, and operating system version, information about how you and your device interact with Lock Screen Magazine, information about operations performed by you after signing in to your HeyTap Account (
such as information about changing your password or the linked mobile number or email address
and the manual account recovery history), the time and duration of your use of Lock Screen Magazine, the search keywords entered by you, and information about events (such as restarts, upgrades, errors, and crashes). We collect such information to verify your identity, analyze the efficiency of our business operations, review transactions, and prevent fraud.
(E)
Lock Screen Magazine offers cloud storage. We will store your information (such as favorites) securely in our cloud solely based on your request.
(F) We may collect information about you such as your device ID, App version, language and region settings, device model, Android SDK version, device resolution, IP address, and User Agent for profiling and behavioral analysis so as to provide you with personalized services, such as displaying and pushing information, products, or services that are more suitable or of more interest to you, or to better implement safeguards. In addition, we may combine your personal information collected via our various services to provide you with an optimal user experience as a whole. To provide you with personalized advertising services, we will share your device ID (GAID) with relevant advertising service providers. If you do not need personalized advertising, please go to the Settings app and tap "Additional settings - Device & privacy - Device ID & ads - Limit ad tracking" to turn off personalized advertising. After you turn off this feature, we will no longer use your information to personalize the content and ads you see, but we may still provide targeted ads and content based on the specific location you have selected or the content of the website you are visiting. Please note that the ads and content we display in this case are solely based on the specific location you have selected or the content of the website you are visiting rather than your identity.
(G) The weather services in Lock Screen Magazine are provided by our partner. To display local weather information on the Lock screen, we will, with your prior express consent, share your IP address with our third-party partner.
(H)To allow you using your favorite photos as wallpapers in Carousel wallpapers, we need to read locally stored photos in your device.
(H)
We will use your personal information solely for the purposes described in this Privacy Notice. Your personal information will only be used for the purposes identified, described, and authorized by you at the time of collection. We will obtain your prior consent if we intend to use your personal information for any purposes other than those specified in this Privacy Notice. We will obtain your prior consent if we intend to use your personal information collected to fulfill a specific purpose for any other purpose. Without your consent, we will not provide your personal information or behavioral data to any third parties.
1.2
We May Collect or Use Your Personal Information Without Your Authorization or Consent
You are fully aware that under applicable laws, we may collect and use your personal information without your authorization or consent under the following circumstances:
(A)
as necessary to fulfill any of our obligations under laws and regulations;
(B)
as necessary to protect national security or national defense;
(C)
as necessary to protect public security, public health, or significant public interests;
(D)
as necessary for criminal investigations, prosecution, trials, or the enforcement of judgments;
(E)
as necessary to safeguard the significant legitimate rights and interests (such as life and property) of you or others, but it is difficult to obtain your authorization or consent;
(F)
the personal information involved is made public by you;
(G)
as necessary to enter into a contract with you or perform a contract entered into between you and us;
(H)
your personal information is collected from legally publicly-disclosed information, such as legal news reports and government information disclosures;
(I)
as necessary for us to maintain the secure and stable operation of Lock Screen Magazine, such as identifying or handling product or service faults;
(J)
as necessary for a news agency to deliver a legal news report;
(K)
as necessary for an academic or research institution to produce statistics or conduct academic research based on public interests, and the personal information contained in the results is de-identified before the results are published.
2.
How We Retain Your Personal Information
The personal information collected by us will be retained for the minimum period needed to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected as described in this Privacy Notice, unless otherwise specified by applicable laws or regulations. We will completely delete or anonymize your personal information upon the expiration of the retention period or when it can be deleted.
If we stop some or all of our products or services for any special reason, we will promptly inform you and stop the collection and processing of your personal information in connection with such products or services, and delete or anonymize your personal information we hold that relates to the products or services, unless otherwise specified by laws and regulations.
3.
How We Share, Transfer or Publicly Disclose Your Personal Information
3.1
How We Share and Transfer Your Personal Information
From time to time, we may share certain personal information with our affiliates and the strategic partners who work with us to provide products and services or otherwise share or transfer your personal information to provide the products or services requested by you.
(A)
Affiliates
: In order for us to provide services to you, we may share your personal information with our affiliates. We will only share necessary personal information
.
If we or our affiliates intend to change the purpose for which your personal information is used and processed, we will obtain your authorization or consent again
.
(B)
Sharing with our authorized partners
: Some of our services will be provided by our authorized partners only for the purposes stated in this Privacy Notice. We may share some of your personal information with our partners in order to provide services to you and improve your user experience
. Specifically:
(1)
We need to share your device information and behavioral data with our advertising and analytics service partners (including but not limited to advertising service providers, third-party ad monitoring service providers, and news feed service providers) in order to implement advertising and monitor the effectiveness of such advertising. We will share your personal information with such authorized partners only to the extent necessary.
(2)
We may need to share your name, mobile number, email address, postal address, bank account number, and Alipay account number with our marketing and promotional partners during, for example, marketing and promotional activities that we entrust our partners to hold or that we hold jointly with the partners. With such information, the partners (third parties) can record your participation in the activities and send you rewards, including but not limited to sending entitlements or mailing rewards. For example, when we need to award you a prize for an activity, we will inform the logistics company of the contact information provided by you during the activity so as to complete the delivery of the prize to you.
(3)
We may need to share your personal information with our service/content providers, including but not limited to cloud service providers, SMS or other technical service providers, payment or financial service providers, and short video content providers, so that they can provide you with the necessary product or service functions. For instance, when we entrust a third-party technical service provider to provide a speech-to-text conversion service, the service provider may receive and store some of your personal information, but they will not use such information for any other purposes.
(4)
In certain circumstances, we will appoint a third party to process your personal information on our behalf. For example, companies that send SMS messages or emails or that provide technical support on our behalf are allowed to use your personal information only to provide you with the relevant services.
(C)
In the event of a merger, acquisition, bankruptcy, or liquidation, if we need to transfer your personal information, we will request the new company or organization to which your personal information will be transferred to continue to be bound by this Privacy Notice; otherwise we will request such company or organization to obtain your authorization or consent again. If there is no need to transfer your personal information, we will fully inform you and delete or anonymize all personal information controlled by us.
We will share or transfer your personal information only for legitimate, proper, necessary, specific, and explicit purposes, and we will only share personal information which is necessary to provide a service. In addition, we will require abovementioned third parties to take considerable confidentiality and security measures during their processing of your personal information by means of agreements or other appropriate measures.
3.2
How We Publicly Disclose Your Personal Information
We will only publicly disclose your personal information:
(A)
With your express consent; or
(B)
When required by law. When we are required to respond to subpoenas or other legal procedures, litigations, or mandatory requirements of government authorities, we may disclose your personal information if we sincerely believe that the disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, ensure the safety of you or others, investigate fraud, or to respond to government requests.
3.3
We May Share, Transfer, or Publicly Disclose Your Personal Information Without Your Authorization or Consent
You are fully aware that under applicable laws, we may share, transfer, or publicly disclose your personal information without your prior authorization or consent under the following circumstances:
(A)
as necessary to fulfill any of our obligations under laws and regulations;
(B)
as necessary to protect national security or national defense;
(C)
as necessary to protect public security, public health, or significant public interests;
(D)
as necessary for criminal investigations, prosecution, trials, or the enforcement of judgments;
(E)
as necessary to safeguard the significant legitimate rights and interests (such as life and property) of you or others, but it is difficult to obtain your authorization or consent;
(F)
the personal information involved is made public by you;
(G)
your personal information is collected from legally publicly-disclosed information, such as legal news reports and government information disclosures.
4.
How We Protect Your Personal Information
4.1
How We Protect Your Personal Information
We adopt technical and organizational measures that are reasonable and actionable to protect the security of the information collected in connection with our services. We have introduced safeguards up to industry standards to protect the personal information provided by you from unauthorized access, disclosure, use, or alteration, or from damage or loss. We will take all reasonable and actionable measures to protect your personal information. For example:
(A)
We use mainstream security means such as SSL to encrypt a variety of services. We regularly review our practices regarding information collection, storage, and processing (including physical security measures) to protect our systems from unauthorized access or alteration.
(B)
We strictly control access to personal information and only grant access to our employees and those of an authorized service provider who need access to personal information in order to help us process such information. These employees are subject to strict contractual confidentiality obligations. If they fail to perform these obligations, they may be held legally liable or be terminated. Personal information access logs will be kept and audited periodically.
(C)
The security of your information is very important to us. Therefore, we will constantly strive to ensure the security of your personal information and implement safeguards such as encrypting stored data and end-to-end encryption during transmission to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. In addition, certain encrypted data is inaccessible to anyone other than the user.
(D)
When transmitting and storing your personal information of special types, we will use security measures such as encryption. Before storing your personal biometric information, we will take technical measures to process it, such as only storing a summary of your personal biometric information.
(E)
We carefully select business partners and service providers and include our requirements for protection of personal information in our business contracts, audits, or assessments.
(F)
We conduct security and privacy protection training, tests, and publicity activities to raise our employees' awareness of the importance of personal information protection.
(G)
We use international and industry-recognized standards to protect your personal information and actively acquire certifications of security and privacy protection.
4.2
Notification and Response to Personal Information Security Events
Please note that although we take reasonable measures to protect your information, no websites, Internet transfers, computer systems, or Wi-Fi connections are absolutely secure. In the event of any security breach of your personal information, we will, pursuant to applicable laws and regulations, promptly notify you of the particulars and possible impact of such breach, the measures taken or to be taken by us, suggestions on how you can prevent and reduce risks, and remedies for you. We will promptly inform you of the information about such breach by email, letter, telephone, or push notification. When it is difficult to inform the personal information subjects concerned one by one, we will issue an announcement in a reasonable and effective manner. We will also report the handling of the event in accordance with the requirements of regulatory authorities.
5.
Your Rights to Your Personal Information
We respect your rights to your personal information. The following lists your rights under law and explains how we will protect your rights.
5.1
Right to Be Informed
We inform you of how we process your personal information by publishing this Privacy Notice and, where required by laws and regulations, by posting a notice or sending you an SMS message or email. We are committed to staying open and transparent about how we use your personal information. You can regularly check this Privacy Notice, receive emails and SMS messages which contain a description of the updates to this Privacy Notice, and contact us in the manner disclosed in this Privacy Notice to learn about our collection and use of your personal information.
5.2
Right of Access
You can directly search for or access your personal information in the user interfaces of our products or services. For example, you can sign in to your account from the relevant product page at any time to access your personal information associated with your account. Specifically:
(A)
You can tap
"Settings -
[
Account
]
- My info"
on your device to access your personal information, such as your name, date of birth, postal address, and the linked mobile number and email address.
If you are unable to search for or access your personal information, or if you encounter any problems when accessing your personal information, you can contact us in the manner disclosed in this Privacy Notice to request access to your personal information.
5.3
Right to Rectification
If you find that any of your personal information processed by us is incorrect or incomplete, you have the right to request us to correct or complete it. You can directly correct and modify parts of your personal information on the relevant feature page of the product or service. Specifically:
(A)
You can tap
"Settings -
[
Account
]
- My info"
on your device to correct your personal information, such as your name, date of birth, postal address, the linked mobile number and email address, and the linked bank card number.
For any personal information that you cannot modify by yourself, you can contact us in the manner disclosed in this Privacy Notice to have such personal information corrected or completed.
5.4
Right to Erasure
You may choose to delete some of the personal information you have submitted to us. You can delete some of your personal information directly on the relevant feature page of the product or service. Specifically:
(A)
You can tap
"Settings -
[
Account
]
- My info"
on your device to delete your personal information, such as your name, date of birth, postal address, the linked mobile number, the linked email address, and the linked bank card number.
For any personal information that you cannot delete by yourself or personal information that you believe to have been collected or used not in compliance with the agreement between you and us, you can contact us in the manner disclosed in this Privacy Notice to have such personal information deleted.
5.5
Right to Delete Your Account
We grant you the right to delete your HeyTap Account.
(A)
You can delete your HeyTap Account by tapping
"
Settings
-
[
Account
]
- Sign-in & security - More help"
on your device
. After you submit a request for deleting your account, we may need to manually review your request in order to make sure that you satisfy the conditions for account deletion, and we will assist you with the deletion of your account within 15 workdays after you submit your request. After your request is approved by us, we will delete or anonymize all your relevant personal information, unless otherwise specified by laws and regulations. After your HeyTap Account is deleted, we will no longer be able to provide you with products or services that are only accessible with a HeyTap Account.
You can also directly contact us in the manner disclosed in this Privacy Notice to request us to delete your HeyTap Account. We will record your request, manually review your request to make sure that you satisfy the conditions for account deletion, and assist you with the deletion of your account within 15 workdays after you submit your request.
5.6
Right to Withdraw Consent
The performance of each service function requires certain basic personal information (see the "How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information" section of this Privacy Notice). You can change the scope of the personal information you authorize us to continue to collect or withdraw your authorization by deleting information, turning off the permissions, changing settings on the product or feature settings page, or deleting your account. Specifically:
(A)
You may withdraw your consent to our use of your device permissions and collection of your personal information by turning off the permissions through "Settings - App management- App list - Lock Screen Magazine".
If you withdraw your consent, we will no longer be able to provide you with related services. We will also no longer process related personal information, but the withdrawal of your consent will not affect the processing of the personal information that has been collected previously.
6.
How We Process Children's Personal Information
Under applicable laws and regulations, you must obtain the consent of your parent or legal guardian before using our products or services if you are under 14. If you are the guardian of a child, before helping the child sign up for or use our products or services, you must carefully read the Children's Privacy Statement (if any) and this Privacy Notice.
Most of the products or services provided by us are not targeted at children under 14 and will not identify the age of users. As for these products and services, we will never use the Internet or other means to collect, store, use, transfer, or disclose personal information about children under 14 without reason. If you are a child under 14 or the parent or legal guardian of a child under 14, or if you find that any information collected, stored, or used by us may contain personal information about a child under 14, you can promptly contact us in the manner disclosed in this Privacy Notice, and we will do everything we can to delete relevant data as soon as possible.
In addition, some of the products or services provided by us may ask users to enter their date of birth in order to identify their age as required by laws and regulations, and we will strictly perform our legal obligation to protect the personal information of children likely to be identified by such products or services. We have developed the Children's Privacy Statement which explains how we collect, use, store, and protect personal information about children. The legal guardians of the underage users shall carefully read the Children's Privacy Statement.
7.
Third-Party Service Providers and Their Services
Our websites, products, apps, and services may contain links to third-party websites, products, or services. You can choose whether to access or use any website, product, or service provided by a third party. For example, the "Follow Us" feature on our official website will guide you to our official social media accounts, where you can find marketing or promotional information posted by us.
We have no control over third-party privacy and data protection policies as such third parties are not bound by this Privacy Notice. Before you submit personal information to third parties, please refer to their privacy policies.
8.
How Your Personal Information Is Transferred Globally
As a company operating globally, we provide products and services through our resources and servers distributed around the world. For the purpose of ensuring the high quality of our services (such as the processing speed) and subject to local data protection laws, we will store your personal data based on the region where your mobile phone is purchased or configured. Our data centers are distributed over France, Singapore, India, and Indonesia. This means that
your personal information may be transferred to or accessed from a jurisdiction outside the country or region where you use the product or service.
You understand that there are different risks under different data protection laws. In this context, we will take measures to ensure that the data collected by us is processed in accordance with this Privacy Notice and applicable laws, and that your personal information is as equally protected as in the country or region where you use a product or service. For example, we will obtain your consent to the cross-border transfer of your personal information, or take security measures such as encryption, de-identification, or entering into a necessary data transfer/sharing agreement with the recipient of your data before transferring such data across borders.
9.
How This Privacy Notice Is Updated
We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Notice from time to time. We will send you update notices through different channels. If you have provided us with your email address, we will notify you of any material changes to this Privacy Notice by email prior to the entry into force of such changes; otherwise we will post a notice on our website or push a notification to you through your device.
This Privacy Notice is subject to adjustments, but without your express consent, we will not diminish your rights under this Privacy Notice.
If you do not agree to this Privacy Notice, we will be unable to collect and use the information necessary to provide a service, which means we will not be able to provide you with the service.
This Privacy Notice shall enter into force as of the date it is updated.
If you have any questions or doubts about this Privacy Notice or our practices, please contact our data protection officer in the manner described below:
